# MDX Component & Content Rules

## MDX Component Pattern (MANDATORY)

Every MDX component MUST use `createMDXComponent` wrapper with Zod schema:

```tsx
import { z } from 'zod';
import { createMDXComponent } from '../../common/create-mdx-component';

const MySchema = z.object({
  title: z.string(),
  variant: z.enum(['a', 'b']).optional().default('a'),
});

function MyComponent({ title, variant }: z.infer<typeof MySchema>) {
  return <div className="...">{title}</div>;
}

export const MDXMyComponent = createMDXComponent(MyComponent, MySchema);
```

After creating a component, register it in `src/mdx/custom-mdx.tsx` components object.

## MDX Component Directory

```
src/mdx/components/{name}/
├── {name}.tsx              # Main component (with createMDXComponent)
├── {name}.module.css       # Optional CSS module
└── use-{hook}.ts           # Optional custom hook
```

## Frontmatter Schema

```yaml
---
title: 'Max 38 characters'
summary: 'Max 40 characters'
description: 'Max 150 characters for SEO'
category: 'react'
publishedAt: '2024-04-30'
image: '/optional.png'
---
```

Zod validation runs at build time — exceeding limits causes build failure.

## Security (DO NOT CHANGE)

In `src/mdx/custom-mdx.tsx`:
- `blockJS: false` — needed for components like MagicMove
- `blockDangerousJS: true` — blocks eval/Function/process/require (CVE-2026-0969)

## Content Directories

- `content/` → blog articles → uses `createMDXProcessor()` → routes to `/article/[slug]`
- `craft/` → experimental → uses `createCraftMDXProcessor()` → routes to `/craft/[slug]`

Do NOT mix content between these directories.
